# ToCSharpFront

## Overview
Agent purpose: transform VB.NET desktop UI (WinForms/WPF) into modern C# Blazor components (Razor + code-behind) for a Blazor front-end `{ProgramName}Front` project targeting .NET 6.

## Instructions
- Convert pages/forms to `{ProgramName}.razor` + `{ProgramName}.razor.cs` (separate code-behind).
- Use `R_BlazorFrontEnd.Controls` components for common widgets.
- Follow patterns for conductor patterns and UI composition.
- Inject `IClientHelper` in the Razor.cs via DI in code-behind, **NOT** in ViewModel.
- Keep UI state inside Razor.cs; viewmodels (if used) should be minimal and only contain non-UI state.
- Maintain data-binding, validation, and interaction contracts.
- Data Validation is allowed only in viewmodels â€” not in `.razor.cs` (code-behind)

## Context (project files to reference)
